putOnWorkspace

public void putOnWorkspace(java.lang.String _targetName,
                           java.lang.Object _object)
Description copied from interface: Workspace
Puts an object on the workspace named by _targetName. Objects that are not already target's are wrapped by an Intercepter object that records changes to the object via its mutator methods. The wrapper will be a subtype of this object. Object's that are placed on the workspace are visible to all the other plans that are active on in this workspace.

Specified by:
putOnWorkspace in interface Workspace
Parameters:
_targetName - the name of the object or event to be put on the workspace.
_object - the Object to be put on the workspace.

putOnWorkspace

public void putOnWorkspace(java.lang.String _targetName)
Description copied from interface: Workspace
Creates a target with no value on the workspace. This method can be used as a simple message passer for plan's. For instance if Plan 9 wanted to let other plan's know that it is completed the target "plan9isCompleted" could be placed on the workspace using this method. Puts a null value on the workspace named by _targetName. null values that are placed on the workspace are visible to all the other plans that are active on in this workspace.

Specified by:
putOnWorkspace in interface Workspace
Parameters:
_targetName - the name of the null value to be put on the workspace.

remove

public java.lang.Object remove(java.lang.String _targetName)
Description copied from interface: Workspace
Removes a target from the workspace. Puts a null value on the workspace named by _targetName. Targets that are removed from the workspace are no longer visible on the workspace to all the other plans that are active on in this workspace. Also the workspace will cease to record changes to this target via its mutator methods.

Specified by:
remove in interface Workspace
Parameters:
_targetName - the name of the target to be removed on the workspace.
Returns:
the target removed from the workspace.
